26:56','2012-05-02 12:26:56',3,176),(794,'E-mail','tamargela@aol.com','2012-05-02 21:51:59','2012-05-02 21:51:59',1,177),(795,'Subject','Summer Dig','2012-05-02 21:51:59','2012-05-02 21:51:59',2,177),(796,'Message','Dear Stuart,\r\nI emailed you a few months ago but got no response.  My daughter and I volunteered for a day last July and now want to come out for two weeks.  We are from Chicago and are very interested in digging.  I (Tamar) dug in Israel many years ago and in the Orkneys for a day a few years ago.  My daughter (Naomi) is 16 and wants to pursue archaeology in college(that in addition to a computer degree to finance her passion !). Here\'s the question:  She wants to pitch a tent--what is usually done about the food ? Is there a store nearby ? And is she old enough to stay on site by herself should I choose a guesthouse ?  Also, I am quite good with a camera--do you need photos taken in addition to digging?  I also hold a Degree in English Literature and a Certificate in Medieval Studies.  I\'d be happy to write, help, dig , or a combination of all ! I look forward to hearing from you soon as we are anxious to book our flights.\r\nTamar Rubinstein','2012-05-02 21:51:59','2012-05-02 21:51:59',3,177),(797,'Name','Warren Moore','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',4,178),(798,'E-mail','wtmoore2005@hotmail.com','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',5,178),(799,'Previous Experience','Yes','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',6,178),(800,'Available From','14/07/2012','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',15,178),(801,'Available To','12/08/2012','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',16,178),(802,'Comments','Student of Cardiff University going into 3rd year. If any spaces are available I\'d like to attend this dig!','2012-05-03 09:56:43','2012-05-03 09:56:43',17,178),(803,'E-mail','r_rudkin@hotmail.com','2012-05-04 12:19:12','2012-05-04 12:19:12',1,179),(804,'Subject','Lost City of Trellech ','2012-05-04 12:19:12','2012-05-04 12: